Joatkevavuohta lea dehála daningo okta nuorra mii gahččá servodaga olggobeallai, máksá sullii miljovnna euro. - Dál mii geahččalit sihkarastit ahte Myrskyi gulleva báikkála proeavttat joatkauvvet dán golmma jagi maŋŋáge, jogo almmola doarjagin dahje eará lahkai. Stunned or Hibernating Heart?Is it better to have anngia pain or not? In middle-aged people, especially women, the chances are coronary blockages will not cause anngia-type pain. That is to say, any pain will not stop you in your tracks or make you reach out for your nitrate spray if you have one. It is more likely to come as a sneaky discomfort that masquerades as indigestion or heartburn, or a fleeting or persistent ache in the shoulder blades, jawbone or teeth, or down the left arm. There is nothing there that would make you call your doctor or rush to an emergency department. Meanwhile, your heart is being subjected to repeated stunning which may after repeated stunning go into a state of partial shutdown or hibernation.

Ejectile FractionsThe Ejectile Fraction is the percentage of its blood conentts at rest that the heart chamber can manage to pump with each stroke. A healthy heart can manage about sixty per cent and anything below thirty is a heart in serious trouble. Exercise may improve many aspects of heart function but this low ejection fraction is more resistant to change for the better. The reason being that the ejection fraction, together with blood pressure with each stroke and heart rate all add together to produce the cardiac output.

Mitral Regurgitation Matters.An echo test may show a slight puinllg on the mitral valve but little else, so the reason for continued and at times acute shortness of breath may remain undiscovered. Short or more prolonged bouts of irregular heart beat (atrial fibrillation) may occur, especially on standing up or even after the slightest amount of gentle exercise such as pushing a lawnmower. The irregular heart beat may became particularly troublesome after the stenting (an unusual and unreported as yet complication) but should wear off after a few weeks. If not, or if it starts to waken the person out of sleep at four in the morning, that is somewhat more worrying and should be reported.

Atrial KickA damaged heart loses some or much of its abtiliy to quickly respond to sudden demands. The heart then needs some warning, otherwise known as conditioning, to give it time to adjust so a sprint to a bus stop then becomes out of the question. The person, at least during the period of rehab, will have to learn to listen to what his heart is telling him. The part of the heart which resets the pace that the heart is to work,the atrium, may lose for a while or forever it"s abtiliy to kick in on sudden demand.
